# DevController HTTP tests for JetBrains HTTP client or other REST clients
# Usage: open this file in IntelliJ/IDEA (HTTP client) and click "Run" on the requests.
# Configure baseUrl and correlationId below if needed.
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@correlationId = 123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000

###
# 1) Create developer (valid)
POST {{baseUrl}}/developers
Content-Type: application/json
correlationId: {{correlationId}}

{
  "fullName": "João Silva",
  "email": "joao.silva3@example.com",
  "nickname": "joaos",
  "uf": "SP",
  "yearsOfExperience": 5,
  "primaryLanguage": "java",
  "interestedInAi": true,
  "skills": ["Spring Boot", "SQL", "REST"]
}

###
# 2) Create developer (duplicate email) - expected 409 CONFLICT when using same email as previous
POST {{baseUrl}}/developers
Content-Type: application/json
correlationId: {{correlationId}}

{
  "fullName": "Maria Santos",
  "email": "joao.silva2@example.com",
  "nickname": "marias",
  "uf": "RJ",
  "yearsOfExperience": 3,
  "primaryLanguage": "java",
  "interestedInAi": false,
  "skills": ["Java", "JUnit"]
}

###
# 3) Create developer (invalid payload) - expected 400 BAD REQUEST
POST {{baseUrl}}/developers
Content-Type: application/json
correlationId: {{correlationId}}

{
  "fullName": "Al",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "nickname": "x",
  "uf": "XX",
  "yearsOfExperience": -1,
  "primaryLanguage": "",
  "interestedInAi": null,
  "skills": []
}

###
# 4) List developers (all)
GET {{baseUrl}}/developers
correlationId: {{correlationId}}

###
# 5) List developers filtered by UF (example SP)
GET {{baseUrl}}/developers?uf=SP
correlationId: {{correlationId}}

###
# 6) List developers filtered by language (case-insensitive)
GET {{baseUrl}}/developers?language=java
correlationId: {{correlationId}}

###
# 7) Get developer by id (replace {id} with the id returned by create, ex: 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/developers/{id}
correlationId: {{correlationId}}

###
# 8) Update experience (PUT) - replace {id} with existing developer id
PUT {{baseUrl}}/developers/{id}/experience
Content-Type: application/json
correlationId: {{correlationId}}

{
  "yearsOfExperience": 10
}

###
# Quick PowerShell/curl examples (replace baseUrl and correlationId as needed):
# Create developer (curl)
# curl -X POST "http://localhost:8080/developers" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -H "correlationId: 123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000" -d '{"fullName":"Teste","email":"teste+ps@example.com","nickname":"teste1","uf":"SP","yearsOfExperience":2,"primaryLanguage":"java","interestedInAi":true,"skills":["Java"]}'

# Note:
# - The controller requires the header `correlationId` (UUID). Use a valid UUID value.
# - Replace {id} placeholders with the actual id returned by the POST response (Location header or response body id).
# - The app must be running (mvnw spring-boot:run) on the configured port (default 8080) for these requests to succeed.

